TITLE: Biden awards Presidential Citizens Medals on two-year anniversary of Jan. 6 Capitol riot
SUMMARY: The ceremony marking the two-year anniversary of the pro-Trump riot was Biden's first time bestowing the Presidential Citizens Medal.

TITLE: U.S. announces $3.8 billion security assistance package for Ukraine, European allies
SUMMARY: The aid package, the 29th such tranche, brings U.S. commitment to Ukraine's fight to about $24.9 billion since the beginning of the Biden administration.

TITLE: SEC ends insider trading probe of ex-Sen. Richard Burr and brother-in-law without taking action, lawyers say
SUMMARY: The Securities and Exchange Commission was eyeing former Sen. Richard Burr over stock sales before a market plunge sparked by the Covid pandemic.

TITLE: U.S. slaps Iran with another round of sanctions over drones used in Russia's war on Ukraine
SUMMARY: The Treasury imposed sanctions on Iran's Qods Aviation Industries, the country's top defense manufacturer, for producing unmanned aerial vehicles.

TITLE: U.S. House adjourns for third night without a speaker as McCarthy scrambles to find deal with far-right Republicans
SUMMARY: The absence of a speaker left the House in disarray, largely due to the fact that rank-and-file members can't be sworn into office until a speaker is elected.

TITLE: South Carolina Supreme Court overturns state 6-week abortion ban as unconstitutional
SUMMARY: The ruling by South Carolina's highest court comes more than six months after the U.S. Supreme Court voided the federal right to abortion.

TITLE: Here's how the House speaker debacle is paralyzing the U.S. Congress
SUMMARY: The failure to elect a House speaker has left the legislative branch of the government effectively paralyzed.

TITLE: Biden to visit U.S.-Mexico border city of El Paso on Sunday as White House rolls out new immigration rules
SUMMARY: The trip details came as the administration announced new border enforcement measures related to the anticipated lifting of the Covid-era Title 42 policy.

TITLE: U.S. House adjourns without a speaker after GOP leader McCarthy loses sixth vote
SUMMARY: Republican House leader Rep. Kevin McCarthy failed six times to secure enough votes to be House speaker, leaving his party in disarray.

TITLE: CVS and Walgreens plan to sell abortion pill mifepristone at pharmacies after FDA rule change
SUMMARY: Mifepristone has become a central flashpoint in the political battle over abortion at the state level in the wake of the Supreme Court overturning Roe v. Wade.

TITLE: Nonprofit financed by billionaire George Soros quietly donated $140 million to political causes in 2021
SUMMARY: A George Soros backed nonprofit put $140 million into politically charged groups in the buildup to the 2022 midterm elections.

TITLE: Feds launch FTX task force to recover victim assets, continue probes as Bankman-Fried pleads not guilty
SUMMARY: The collapse of crypto exchange FTX led to criminal prosecutions of founder Sam Bankman-Fried and two of his lieutenants in New York federal court.

TITLE: U.S. House adjourns without a speaker after GOP leader Kevin McCarthy falls short in three votes
SUMMARY: After months of lobbying fellow Republicans, GOP Leader Kevin McCarthy failed in three rounds of voting to win the 218 votes he needs to become House speaker.

TITLE: Trump's tax returns released by House Ways and Means Committee
SUMMARY: The House Ways and Means Committee released former President Donald Trump's tax returns after a yearslong legal battle.

TITLE: Southwest warns of more flight cancellations as meltdown draws federal scrutiny
SUMMARY: Bitter cold, high winds and snow sparked cascading flight cancellations and delays over the holiday weekend.

TITLE: Supreme Court extends Trump-era pandemic immigration rule to allow quicker deportations
China to scrap quarantine for international travelers in an essential end of zero-Covid
SUMMARY: China announced Monday that starting Jan. 8, 2023, travelers will no longer need to quarantine upon arrival on the mainland.

TITLE: New sanctions starting to bite Russia's economy as Moscow admits deficit impact
SUMMARY: The latest round of Western sanctions against Russia over its invasion of Ukraine are beginning to pinch the country's economy, economists have suggested.

TITLE: U.S. House passes $1.7 trillion bill funding federal government through September, sending it to Biden
SUMMARY: The bill provides $772.5 billion for discretionary programs and $858 billion in defense funding. It now goes to President Joe Biden to be signed into law.

TITLE: Jan. 6 House committee releases final report on Trump Capitol riot investigation
SUMMARY: The Jan. 6 panel voted this week to refer Trump to the DOJ for possible prosecution over efforts to overturn his election loss to President Joe Biden.

TITLE: Senate passes $1.7 trillion government funding bill, teeing up House vote
SUMMARY: The Senate passed a $1.7 trillion omnibus bill that funds all government agencies and the Pentagon for the next year. Now it heads to the House.

TITLE: Biden urges Americans to travel early if possible with a massive blizzard slated to hit the U.S.
SUMMARY: "This is not like a snow day when you were a kid," Biden said. "This is serious stuff."

TITLE: New bill will force Twitter, TikTok and other social media platforms to increase transparency by sharing internal data
SUMMARY: Senators introduced a bill targeting the lack of transparency among social media companies even as lawmakers consider banning some platforms in the U.S.

TITLE: IRS was 'asleep at the wheel' for failing to audit Trump tax returns, Senate Finance chair says
SUMMARY: Wyden's assessment followed a report that the IRS had only started one mandatory audit of Trump's tax returns during his four years as president.

TITLE: Zelenskyy meets with Biden on his first known wartime trip outside Ukraine
SUMMARY: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy met with President Joe Biden at the White House ahead of a speech to a joint session of Congress.

TITLE: Read how much Trump paid — or didn't pay — in taxes each year
SUMMARY: Donald Trump has guarded his income tax returns from public disclosure. A House committee has voted to release them in redacted form.

TITLE: Only one Trump tax return as president got mandatory IRS audit, report says
SUMMARY: A report on Donald Trump's federal income taxes was released after a House panel voted to make public redacted copies of his tax returns.

TITLE: White House and Congress prepare for possible visit from Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy, sources say
SUMMARY: Ukrainian President Zelenskyy could address a joint session of Congress in the House chamber on Wednesday, according to sources familiar.

TITLE: House probe of Jan. 6 pro-Trump riot is cooperating with DOJ special counsel, reports say
SUMMARY: The Jan. 6 committee's reportedly extensive cooperation was revealed after the panel voted to refer Trump to the DOJ for possible criminal prosecution.

TITLE: DOJ says over 3,000 U.S. minors were targeted in ‘sextortion’ crimes in the past year
SUMMARY: "Sextortion," a type of online enticement where predators extort minors for sexual content or money, is on the rise, federal law enforcement officials said.
